@node whatsnew "What's New!"

Version 2.85  15 June 1997

   When you use "Review Invoice" , "Print Invoice" or 
   "Print Statement". It now uses a list view to display the Invoice
   number along with the customer name and date. Makes life a lot
   easier.

   Invoicer uses the page width settings from the Printer preferences
   so it will centre properly. IE If you are using condensed (15/17)
   with a page width of 135 characters etc.

Version 2.87    20 June 1997

   When you entering an invoice inputing 'ZZZ' into the item code
   enables you to enter upto 18 lines of text. 
   
   Removed some bugs in 'Print Statement' where the statement number
   was incorrect.

   Added CLOCK tooltype.

Version 2.88  29 April 1998

   Removed support for tooltypes. Now uses Invoicer.prefs. Use
   a text editor to change.

Version 2.89 20 August 1998

   Reorganised some of the menu items. Added 'Preferences' to the 
   Edit menu. Re-vamped the help/amigaguide file. Changed the look
   and feel.
   Added some limited screenmodes. Accessable from Invoicer.guide

Version 2.91

	Invoicer 2.91 A Update and bug fix.



  Bug Fixes:

	Entering invoice cursor moves down one line to many after
	the date is entered. 

	Label Printing: Displays the window properly and shows
	the Deliver too address.

	Prints a blank invoice okay now

	Does not go balistic if the Invoice directory(in Invoicer.prefs)
	does not exist.

  Update:

	/*Specify the length of the Code field, also the description is 
	proportional to the length of the code field.*/

	To do this properly all Invoice printing is done using Elite
	This gives a line length of 96 columns as opposed to 80
	previously. This means that you can no longer rely on Topaz
	so Invoicer requires XEN.font to be in your fonts directory.
	Not to worry as this is supplied.
       =============================================================

	/*Be able to Save a invoice with a unique name and then add data
	at a later time*/

	NEW MENU ITEM: Invoice/AddData.
	
	i.	This allows you to load a previously saved Invoice 
		and then add data to the end.

	ii.	Print a previously saved invoice.
       =============================================================

	/*Preferences*/

	Created a seperate program to edit preferences.

        ==========================================================



@endnode

@node trbl "TROUBLE SHOOTING"

Q:  Why can't I print an Invoice?

A:  You will need to either load or create a file. For this you
    will have to enter: YOUR Company Details, Goods/Item details
    and Customer details.

Q:  I have done the above but I still can't print an invoice!

A:  Check the printer is turned on. Check cables.
    Check Printer Driver.

Q:  I have not got a battery backed up clock. How can I set the
    date correctly?

A:  From Invoicer.info edit the tooltypes SETDATE=y.
    This will run the Time Preferences each time Invoicer is run.

Q:  On printing multiple invoices, the invoices creep down the page!

A:  Set the pagelength from the printer preferences correctly. Or
    set the tooltype PAGELENGTH=<>.

Q:  When I print an invoice it does not centre my company title.
    The title is not in double width or bold!

A:  Invoicer uses standard ANSI codes, your printer/driver may
    not be able to use this function.

Q:  How can I show my apreciation for such a wonderful progam as
    Invoicer?

A:  Send the author: some MONEY!, A1200, A4000, A3000!!!

Q:  Can Invoicer automatically load a file when first run?

A:  Yes. Edit the tooltype LOAD=<filename> where <filename>
    is the file you wish to load. Or from cli:
    invoicer <filename>, this would be useful from a program
    such as TOOLDAEMON ©Nico Francois.

Q:  I edited my customer/item databases. When I next run Invoicer
    I found I had lost the changes. What happened?

A:  After you add/edit or create an invoice you should always either
    Save the data or exit from Invoicer before you turn your Amiga
    off. This way the changes will be saved to disk!

Q:  Is there a version of Invoicer for other makes of computers?

A:  Yes. For the PC. @{"Contact" link shareware} me direct for more information.

Q:  I have tried altering the Printer Preferences so I have a page 
    length more than 66 but Invoicer seems to ignore this why?

A:  You may have the Tooltype 'Pagelength' set to 66. Alter/delete
    this and it should be Ok.

Q:  Invoicer doesn't work. When I run the program it says it is not
    comaptible with NTSC-Hires?

A:  Use the supplied program 'ScreenMode' and select a suitable screen mode
    for Invoicer

@endnode
@node gui2 "TOOLS"
   Invoicer reads some data from the Invoicer.prefs  file

   These are:

      DATE     This will change the date formats
            INPUT 0-4  DD.MM.YYYY, MM.DD.YYYY
            {Not implemented yet}

      CURRENCY Enter the Currency you use.

      COPIES      How many copies to print.{Default 1}

      REQ      INPUT y or n .
            If you have your printer prefs set
            for Single and REQ=Y then before
            printing Invoicer displays a requester
            asking you to insert a sheet of paper.
            If you have a Sheet Feeder then set
            REQ=N so there will be no requester.

      PATH     Enter a path to save your invoices.
            Every time you print a Invoice Invoicer
            saves a copy to disk. To save cluttering
            up your Invoicer directory you can
            specify where to save the invoices.

      PAGELENGTH  You specify the pagelength in case you
            have any problems in positioning your
            invoices at print time.

      SETDATE  If set to SETDATE=Y then when first run
            Invoicer will display the Time Preference
            program so you can set the Date.
            Obviously if you have battery backed clock
            then you will never need to use this
            function.
            For SETDATE to work you will require the
            Time preference program to be in your
            SYS:prefs drawer.

      LOAD     LOAD=[Filename] . This will load the file
            [Filename] when you first run Invoicer

      READER      READER=multiview. Enter your amigaguide
            reader. This will be either Amigaguide
            (WB2.04-2.1) or Multiview (WB3.0-3.1)
            Normally it is in the SYS:utilities
            drawer.

                AUTOSAVE        AUTOSAVE=Y. This will save any changes as
                                you make them.


      CLOCK    Set to CLOCK=Y will display the date and
            time in the window title.
            NOTE: With this set Invoicer will no longer
            wait if you run other applications.

      EDITOR      Set the editor (defaults to ed)

      CODE	Set the CODE field length. If this does not exist use
		a text editor to add it.

Use a text editor to change/edit. Or use the 'Preference' from Edit.

@endnode


