@node statement "STATEMENT"

  SYNOPSIS:  Create/Print Statement of overdue Invoices


  SHORTCUT:  RCOMMAND M


   You select the customer for the statement. Then you have the
   opportunity to select the invoice for the statement.
   
   When you have selected all the invoices you require just select
   'Cancel' from the filerequester.
   
   If however you select a invoice that was not issued to the customer
   you can either:
   
   'Change'.   This will change the customer to the customer of this
          Invoice.

   'Exit'.      This will not accept this invoice and will go onto the
          next operation.

   'Continue'. This will ignore the problem and just add this invoice
          to the list.
   
   
   Now you can enter upto 16 lines of text. When you have finished
   either press 'Esc' or click the Close Window gadget.
   
   Now you can print the statement.


@endnode

@NODE install "Install Invoicer!"

   Installing  Invoicer is simple.  Just drag the Invoicer drawer
    onto your  hard  drive.   There are no special assigns.
   Just make sure you have the reqtools.library correctly installed 
   (if not it is supplied).

   You will need XEN font in your fonts drawer. It is supplied.

   Or you can install it below:


   @{"Install Invoicer on your Hard Drive!" system hdinstall}


   @{"Install different screenmode" link screenmode}


@endnode
@node screenmode "Install ScreenMode!"


Invoicer can use 3 Screenmodes. 

   Pal Hires      640x256
   Pal Hires Laced      640x512

   NTSC Hires Laced  640x400

You can get Invoicer to open on the WorkBench screen by deleting
INVOICERSCREEN program.

 You can select the screenmode right now: 

@{"ScreenMode:" system screenmode}


Have fun!


@endnode

